cember 2018 |date=July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"DWPWCAOutocmesESA\">{{cite web |title=Employment and Support Allowance: Work Capability Assessments, Mandatory Reconsiderations and Appeals |url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/716083/esa-wca-summary-june-2018.pdf |website=assets.publishing.service.gov.uk |publisher=Department for Work and Pensions |accessdate=2 January 2019 |format=PDF |date=14 June 2018}}</ref> that assessors were pressured to find claimants fit for work when they did not feel they were,<ref name=\"WCAOralEvidenceESA\">{{cite web |title=Work and Pensions Committee Oral evidence: Employment and Support Allowance and Work Capability Assessments, HC 1212 |url=http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/work-and-pensions-committee/employment-and-support-allowance-and-work-capability-assessments/oral/9582.html |website=data.parliament.uk |publisher=The Stationery Office |accessdate=25 December 2018 |location=London |date=14 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"FranklinESA\">{{cite web |last1=Franklin |first1=Kaliya |title=Investigating the real reason for the misery of \u2018 fit for work \u2019assessments |url=https://www.centreforwelfarereform.org/uploads/attachment/400/how-norms-become-targets.pdf |website=Centre for Welfare Reform |publisher=Centre for Welfare Reform |accessdate=25 December 2018 |format=PDF |date=2013}}</ref><ref name=\"GillonESA\">{{cite news |last1=Gillon |first1=David |title=How Atos comes under pressure to declare disabled people as fit for work {{!}} David Gillon |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/dec/09/atos-disabled-people-assessment-fit-work-report |accessdate=25 December 2018 |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian Media Group Limited |date=9 December 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"BBCWCAUnfairESA\">{{cite news |title=Disability benefit assessments 'unfair' |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/uk-22561006/disability-benefit-assessments-unfair-says-ex-worker |accessdate=25 December 2018 |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=16 May 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"RameshESA\">{{cite news |last1=Ramesh |first1=Randeep |title=Atos benefit claimants face biased medical assessments, doctor alleges |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2013/may/16/atos-doctor-claimants-biased-medical-assessments |accessdate=25 December 2018 |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian Media Group Limited |date=16 May 2013}}</ref> that ESA is being used to conceal unemployment levels,<ref name=\"SHUESA\">{{cite book |last1=Beatty |first1=Christina |last2=Fothergill |first2=Steve |last3=Gore |first3=Tony |title=The Real Level of Unemployment 2017 |date=2017 |publisher=Sheffield Hallam University |location=Sheffield |pages=3, 6-9,12-13 |url=https://shura.shu.ac.uk/17175/1/Beatty-TheRealLevelOfUnemployment2017%28VoR%29.pdf |accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ElliotESA\">{{cite news |last1=Elliott |first1=Larry |title=Sparkling employment figures mask real picture of UK economy |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/oct/29/sparkling-jobless-figures-mask-real-picture-uk-economy-unemployed |accessdate=31 December 2018 |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian News and Media Limited |date=29 October 2017}}</ref> that some people were too sick or disabled to work but could not claim because they had not paid enough National Insurance contributions but their household income was too high,<ref name=\"RyanESA2\">{{cite news |last1=Ryan |first1=Frances |title=Denise worked all her life. Then she got ill \u2013 and the state pulled away the safety net {{!}} Frances Ryan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/oct/20/worked-hard-became-ill-state-safety-net |accessdate=23 December 2018 |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian Media Group Limited |date=20 October 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"DWPReportESA3\">{{cite book |last1=Barnes |first1=Helen |last2=Oakley |first2=Joy |last3=Stevens |first3=Helen |last4=Sissons |first4