f dead' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/patrick-butler-cuts-blog/2014/jul/24/stuck-in-dwp-limbo-better-off-dead-mandatory-reconsideration |accessdate=23 December 2018 |work=The Guardian |publisher=Guardian Media Group Limited |date=24 July 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"BarnesEtAlReport4\">{{cite book |last1=Barnes |first1=Helen |last2=Oakley |first2=Joy |last3=Stevens |first3=Helen |last4=Sissons |first4=Paul |title=Unsuccessful Employment and Support Allowance claims \u2013 qualitative research |date=2011 |publisher=Department for Work and Pensions |isbn=978-1-908523-05-1 |pages=19-21 |url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/214543/rrep762.pdf |accessdate=25 December 2018}}</ref> that claimants were not incentivised to work,<ref name=\"GrovesESA\">{{cite news |last1=Groves |first1=Jason |title=We can get one million claimants off benefit says Iain Duncan Smith |url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3208300/We-one-million-claimants-disability-benefit-work-says-Iain-Duncan-Smith.html |accessdate=23 December 2018 |work=Mail Online |publisher=Associated Newspapers Limited |date=24 August 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"PhilpESA\">{{cite book |last1=Philp |first1=Chris |title=Work for the Dole A proposal to fix welfare dependency |date=2013 |publisher=The TaxPayer's Allowance |url=https://d3n8a8pro7vhmx.cloudfront.net/taxpayersalliance/pages/452/attachments/original/1423653195/workforthedole.pdf?1423653195 |accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"BeckfordWCA\">{{cite web |last1=Beckford |first1=Martin |title=\u00a3435MILLION in sickness benefit handed to drunks and drug addicts |url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2934798/435MILLION-sickness-benefit-handed-drunks-junkies-75-000-signed-work-addictions-given-108-week.html |website=Mail Online |publisher=Associated Newspapers Ltd |accessdate=22 December 2018 |date=1 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"KirkupWCA\">{{cite news |last1=Kirkup |first1=Ja