overnment/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/49779/sayce-report.pdf |website=assets.publishing.service.gov.uk |publisher=Department for Work and Pensions |accessdate=25 December 2018 |date=June 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"HoCReportESA3\">{{cite web |title=House of Commons - The role of incapacity benefit reassessment in helping claimants into employment - Work and Pensions Committee |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201012/cmselect/cmworpen/1015/101510.htm#note254 |website=publications.parliament.uk |publisher=Parliament.UK |accessdate=25 December 2018 |date=26 July 2011}}</ref> that some claimants did not receive enough money to cover their living costs,<ref name=\"DBCESA\">{{cite web |title=Almost 70% of disabled people say cuts to ESA will cause their health to suffer and half may return to work later |url=https://disabilitybenefitsconsortium.wordpress.com/2015/10/27/almost-70-of-disabled-people-say-cuts-to-esa-will-cause-their-health-to-suffer-and-half-may-return-to-work-later/ |website=Disability Benefits Consortium |publisher=Disability Benefits Consortium |accessdate=26 December 2018 |language=en |date=27 October 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"StoneESA\">{{cite news |last1=Stone |first1=John |title=The DWP is cutting a disability benefit that already leaves a third of recipients unable to afford food |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/the-government-is-cutting-a-disability-benefit-that-already-leaves-a-third-of-recipients-unable-to-a6764641.html |accessdate=26 December 2018 |work=The Independent |publisher=The Independent |date=8 December 2015 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"BateEtAlESA\">{{cite web |last1=Bate |first1=Alex |last2=Keen |first2=Richard |last3=Kennedy |first3=Steven |last4=Murphy |first4=Chris |title=Abolition of the ESA Work-Related Activity Component |url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-7649 |website=researchbriefings.parliament.uk |publisher=Parliament.UK |accessdate=26 December 