oman Dies After Being Judged 'Fit For Work' |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/05/28/linda-wootton-dies-after-being-judged-fit-for-work_n_3346582.html |accessdate=26 December 2018 |work=HuffPost UK |publisher=Oath Inc. |date=28 May 2013 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"DeGraafESA\">{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2592214/We-wrong-Government-admits-not-axed-disability-benefits-Aspergers-sufferer-starved-death-just-four-months-later-weighing-five-half-stone.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | first=Mia | last=De Graaf |title='We were wrong': Government admits it should not have axed disability benefits of Asperger's sufferer who starved to death just five months later weighing five-and-a-half stone | date=29 March 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"GuardianWCAdeathESA\">{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/feb/28/man-starved-to-death-after-benefits-cut | location=London |work= The Guardian |title=Vulnerable man starved to death after benefits were cut | date=28 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"ITVESA\">{{cite web|title=Government welfare advisor did not know about 2010 suicide 'triggered by work assessment'|publisher=ITV News|date=9 November 2015|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2015-11-09/government-welfare-advisor-did-not-know-about-2010-suicide-triggered-by-work-assessment/}}</ref><ref name=\"DailyRecordESA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/heartbroken-dad-blames-benefits-axemen-2292176|title=Heartbroken dad blames benefits axemen for driving his ill son to commit suicide|author=Craig McDonald|date=22 September 2013|work=dailyrecord|accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Disabilitynewsservice\">{{cite web|date=28 July 2016|title=Parents of 'fit for work' suicide man back call for prosecution|publisher=Disability News Service|url=http://www.disabilitynewsservice.com/parents-of-fit-for-work-suicide-man-back-call-for-iain-duncan-smith-prosecution/}}</ref><ref name=DNSSuicideESA>{{cite 