{"title_page": "Philippine Airlines Flight 215", "text_new": "{{short description|1970 airplane bombing}}\n{{Infobox Aircraft accident\n|name    = Philippine Airlines Flight 215\n|image   = File:Philippine Airlines Hawker Siddeley HS-748 Srs2-209 RP-C1023 (29721944592).jpg\n|caption = A [[Hawker Siddeley HS 748]] similar to the one involved.\n|occurrence_type=Bombing\n|date    = April 21, 1970\n|type    = Bomb explosion\n|site    = [[Philippine Islands]]\n|coords  = \n|aircraft_type = [[Hawker Siddeley 748|Hawker Siddeley HS-748-209 Srs. 2]]\n|aircraft_name = \n|operator      = [[Philippine Airlines]]\n|tail_number   = PI-C1022<ref name=\"ASN\">{{ASN accident|id=19700421-0|type=Criminal Occurrence}}</ref>\n|origin        = [[Cauayan Airport]], [[Cauayan City]], [[Philippines]]\n|destination   = [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila International Airport]], [[Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n|passengers    = 32\n|crew          = 4\n|fatalities    = 36\n|survivors     = 0\n}}\n\n'''Philippine Airlines Flight 215''' was the route designator for a [[Philippine Airlines]] flight from [[Cauayan Airport]] to [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila International Airport]] which exploded en route to [[Manila]].\n\n==Accident==\n\nOn April 21, 1970, Flight 215 was en route from [[Cauayan Airport]] to [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila Airport]] when, at 10,500  [[Foot (length)|ft]], an explosion occurred in the aircraft's lavatory, the tail section separated from the aircraft and the aircraft crashed.<ref name=\"ASN\" />\n\nAll 32 passengers and 4 crew (36 in total) were killed in the incident.<ref name=\"ASN\" /> A bomb in the lavatory was the suspected cause of the incident.<ref>[http://www.airsafe.com/events/airlines/pal.htm ''Fatal Events Since 1970 for Philippine Air Lines'']</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{coord missing|Philippines}}\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines}}\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in 1970}}{{aviation-accident-stub}}\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 1970]]\n[[Category:Philippine Airlines accidents and incidents|215]]\n[[Category:Airliner bombings]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 1970]]\n[[Category:Accidents and incidents involving the Hawker Siddeley HS 748]]\n[[Category:1970 in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:April 1970 events in Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1970 airplane bombing}}\n{{Infobox Aircraft accident\n|name    = Philippine Airlines Flight 215\n|image   = File:Philippine Airlines Hawker Siddeley HS-748 Srs2-209 RP-C1023 (29721944592).jpg\n|caption = A [[Hawker Siddeley HS 748]] similar to the one involved.\n|occurrence_type=Bombing\n|date    = April 21, 1970\n|type    = Bomb Explosion\n|site    = [[Philippine Islands]]\n|coords  = \n|aircraft_type = [[Hawker Siddeley 748|Hawker Siddeley HS-748-209 Srs. 2]]\n|aircraft_name = \n|operator      = [[Philippine Airlines]]\n|tail_number   = PI-C1022<ref name=\"ASN\">{{ASN accident|id=19700421-0|type=Criminal Occurrence}}</ref>\n|origin        = [[Cauayan Airport]], [[Cauayan City]], [[Philippines]]\n|destination   = [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila International Airport]], [[Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n|passengers    = 32\n|crew          = 4\n|fatalities    = 36\n|survivors     = 0\n}}\n\n'''Philippine Airlines Flight 215''' was the route designator for a [[Philippine Airlines]] flight from [[Cauayan Airport]] to [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila International Airport]] which exploded en route to [[Manila]].\n\n==Accident==\n\nOn April 21, 1970, Flight 215 was en route from [[Cauayan Airport]] to [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila Airport]] when, at 10,500  [[Foot (length)|ft]], an explosion occurred in the aircraft's lavatory, the tail section separated from the aircraft and the aircraft crashed.<ref name=\"ASN\" />\n\nAll 32 passengers and 4 crew (36 in total) were killed in the incident.<ref name=\"ASN\" /> A bomb in the lavatory was the suspected cause of the incident.<ref>[http://www.airsafe.com/events/airlines/pal.htm ''Fatal Events Since 1970 for Philippine Air Lines'']</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{coord missing|Philippines}}\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines}}\n{{Aviation accidents and incidents in 1970}}{{aviation-accident-stub}}\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 1970]]\n[[Category:Philippine Airlines accidents and incidents|215]]\n[[Category:Airliner bombings]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 1970]]\n[[Category:Accidents and incidents involving the Hawker Siddeley HS 748]]\n[[Category:1970 in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:April 1970 events in Asia]]\n", "name_user": "Rodney Baggins", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:MOS:CAPS", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippine_Airlines_Flight_215"}
{"title_page": "Shram Shakti Express", "text_new": "[[File:Shram Shakti Express Newly LHBfied.jpg|alt=VVIP Non Stop Night Rider of NCR|thumb|Brand New LHB Rakes of VVIP Shram Shakti Express]]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=March 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name= Shram Shakti Express\n| image= Shram Shakti Express Newly LHBfied.jpg\n| caption=Shram Shakti Express\nThe Non Stop Superfast Express\nThe Night Rider of NCR\nVVIP Train Between/For\nNew Delhi-Kanpur Central \nNo.1 Punctual Train\nQueen of NCR \n| type= Superfast\n| State= [[Delhi]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| last=\n| operator=NCR\n| start= [[Kanpur Central]]\n| stops= [[Panki railway station|Panki Dham]]\n| end= [[New Delhi Railway Station]]\n| distance= {{convert|440|km|miles}}\n| journeytime= 6&nbsp;hrs 45&nbsp;mins\n(for 12451)\n& 6&nbsp;hrs 35&nbsp;mins\n(for 12452)\n| frequency= Daily\n| class= 1st, 2nd & 3rd AC, Sleeper, General\n| seating= Yes\n| sleeping= Yes\n| catering= None\n| gauge= {{RailGauge|1676mm|lk=on|allk=on}}\n| Observation facility=LHB Rakes. hi\n| trainnumber= 12451 / 12452\n| speed= Maximum {{convert|110|kph|mph}}\nAverage {{convert|65|kph|mph}}\n| map= [[File:Shram Shakti Express (Kanpur - New Delhi) Shatabdi Express route map.png|250px|Shram Shakti Express (Kanpur - New Delhi) route map]]\n}}\nThe '''Shram Shakti Express''' is an [[Indian Railways]] Super fast train which runs non-stop overnight between the cities of [[Kanpur]] and [[New Delhi]]. It is the longest train of [[North Central Railway]], with 22 coaches. It covers the 440&nbsp;km distance in little more than 6 hours in the night.\nIt has 2 rakes, one train starts at New Delhi (NDLS) at 23:55 from PF no-12, and another train starts at Kanpur Central (CNB) at 23:55 from PF no-1. It gets fully LHB Fied on 24 July 2018.\nIt is often called Queen of NCR. It enjoys top priority along with [[Prayagraj Express]] and [[Shiv Ganga Express]]. It is Night rider of NCR, running non stop between New Delhi and [[Panki railway station|Panki Dham]] (station serving Western Kanpur), almost 429 km(11 km before Kanpur Central).\nIt is a super fast express train runs overnight between NDLS-CNB. \nIt has two dedicated LHB rakes, no rake sharing. \nShramshakti and [[Kanpur\u2013New Delhi Shatabdi Express]] are two dedicated intercity trains for/between New Delhi (NDLS) and Kanpur Central (CNB). Another train is [[Kanpur Central\u2013Anand Vihar Terminal Express]] a weekly train between [[Anand Vihar Terminal railway station|Anand Vihar Terminal]] (ANVT), New Delhi to Kanpur Central.\n\n<br />\n\n== LHBfication ==\nOn 29 July 2018, replacing the old ICF coaches, Shram Shakti Express got new German LHB rakes with a total of 22 coaches. Modern [[LHB Coaches]] with a MPS (Maximum Permissible Speed) of 160 Kmph are more comfortable. The new coaches, based on a German technology Linke Hoffman Busch (LHB), are made of stainless steel which do not turn turtle during accidents. The light-weight coaches will also improve the train's speed. Bigger windows, biotoilets, lamps at all AC seats and sound insulation are the other features.\n\n== Coaches ==\nShram Shakti Express runs with 1 AC 1 tier coach, 1 AC 2 tier coaches, 4 AC 3 tier coaches, 9 Sleeper coaches, 5 General coaches along with 2 EOG coaches. Thus, having a total of 22 LHB coaches. \n<br />\n\n== Traction ==\nThe normal locomotive of '''Shram Shakti''' is a [[Indian locomotive class WAP-7|WAP 4]] Locomotive of Kanpur shed. However due to non availability of WAP 4, it may sometimes get WAP 5 or WAP 7 of Kanpur locoshed.  \n\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Sleeper Class coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - Sleeper Class coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 1st class coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 1st class coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General Deen Dayalu coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - General [[Deendayal Upadhyaya|Deen Dayalu coach]]\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board 2.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board 2\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach.jpg\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express - AC 2 tier.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express.jpg\nFile:Shram Shakti Express.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== Coaches ==\n[[Passenger car (rail)|Coach]] Composition are as follows-\n\n12451 CNB-NDLS\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| Loco\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 1\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 2\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 3\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 4\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 5\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 6\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 7\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 8\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 9\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 10\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 11\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 12\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 13\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 14\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 15\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 16\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 17\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 18\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 19\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 20\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 21\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 22\n|-\n|[[File:BSicon LDER.svg|25px]] ||EOG||GEN||GEN||GEN||GEN||GEN||B1||B2||B3||B4||A1||H1||S1||S2||S3||S4||S5||S6||S7||S8||S9||EOG\n|}\n\n12452 NDLS-CNB\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| Loco\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 1\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 2\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 3\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 4\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 5\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 6\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 7\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 8\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 9\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 10\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 11\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 12\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 13\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 14\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 15\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 16\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 17\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 18\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 19\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 20\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 21\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 22\n|-\n|[[File:BSicon LDER.svg|25px]] ||EOG||S9||S8||S7||S6||S5||S4||S3||S2||S1||H1||A1||B4||B3||B2||B1||GEN||GEN||GEN||GEN||GEN||EOG\n|}\n\nLoco in-charge for this train is [[WAP-4]] [[Kanpur Central railway station|Kanpur]] (CNB) Shed.\n\n'''<big>Non Stop Earlier</big>'''\n\nIt was used to run non stop over night between New Delhi and Kanpur Central.\n\nBut later it had given a halt at Panki in Kanpur. It is non stop over night train. Very punctual and clean also. This along with Kanpur Shatabdi  are two trains from/to NDLS-CNB.\n\n \n\n==External links==\n*[http://etrain.info/in?TRAIN=12451 Shram Shakti Express (Kanpur to New Delhi)]\n*[http://etrain.info/in?TRAIN=12452 Shram Shakti Express (New Delhi to Kanpur)]\n\n{{Railways in Northern India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shram Shakti Express}}\n[[Category:Named passenger trains of India]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Railway services introduced in 2002]]\n[[Category:Transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Transport in Kanpur]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Shram Shakti Express Newly LHBfied.jpg|alt=VVIP Non Stop Night Rider of NCR|thumb|Brand New LHB Rakes of VVIP Shram Shakti Express]]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=March 2011}}\n\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name= Shram Shakti Express\n| image= 12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier coach.jpg\n| caption=Shram Shakti Express\nThe Non Stop Superfast Express\nThe Night Rider of NCR\nVVIP Train Between/For\nNew Delhi-Kanpur Central \nNo.1 Punctual Train\nQueen of NCR \n| type= Superfast\n| State= [[Delhi]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| last=\n| operator=NCR\n| start= [[Kanpur Central]]\n| stops= [[Panki railway station|Panki Dham]]\n| end= [[New Delhi Railway Station]]\n| distance= {{convert|440|km|miles}}\n| journeytime= 6&nbsp;hrs 45&nbsp;mins\n(for 12451)\n& 6&nbsp;hrs 35&nbsp;mins\n(for 12452)\n| frequency= Daily\n| class= 1st, 2nd & 3rd AC, Sleeper, General\n| seating= Yes\n| sleeping= Yes\n| catering= None\n| gauge= {{RailGauge|1676mm|lk=on|allk=on}}\n| Observation facility=LHB Rakes. hi\n| trainnumber= 12451 / 12452\n| speed= Maximum {{convert|110|kph|mph}}\nAverage {{convert|65|kph|mph}}\n| map= [[File:Shram Shakti Express (Kanpur - New Delhi) Shatabdi Express route map.png|250px|Shram Shakti Express (Kanpur - New Delhi) route map]]\n}}\nThe '''Shram Shakti Express''' is an [[Indian Railways]] Super fast train which runs non-stop overnight between the cities of [[Kanpur]] and [[New Delhi]]. It is the longest train of [[North Central Railway]], with 22 coaches. It covers the 440&nbsp;km distance in little more than 6 hours in the night.\nIt has 2 rakes, one train starts at New Delhi (NDLS) at 23:55 from PF no-12, and another train starts at Kanpur Central (CNB) at 23:55 from PF no-1. It gets fully LHB Fied on 24 July 2018.\nIt is often called Queen of NCR. It enjoys top priority along with [[Prayagraj Express]] and [[Shiv Ganga Express]]. It is Night rider of NCR, running non stop between New Delhi and [[Panki railway station|Panki Dham]] (station serving Western Kanpur), almost 429 km(11 km before Kanpur Central).\nIt is a super fast express train runs overnight between NDLS-CNB. \nIt has two dedicated LHB rakes, no rake sharing. \nShramshakti and [[Kanpur\u2013New Delhi Shatabdi Express]] are two dedicated intercity trains for/between New Delhi (NDLS) and Kanpur Central (CNB). Another train is [[Kanpur Central\u2013Anand Vihar Terminal Express]] a weekly train between [[Anand Vihar Terminal railway station|Anand Vihar Terminal]] (ANVT), New Delhi to Kanpur Central.\n\n<br />\n\n== LHBfication ==\nOn 29 July 2018, replacing the old ICF coaches, Shram Shakti Express got new German LHB rakes with a total of 22 coaches. Modern [[LHB Coaches]] with a MPS (Maximum Permissible Speed) of 160 Kmph are more comfortable. The new coaches, based on a German technology Linke Hoffman Busch (LHB), are made of stainless steel which do not turn turtle during accidents. The light-weight coaches will also improve the train's speed. Bigger windows, biotoilets, lamps at all AC seats and sound insulation are the other features.\n\n== Coaches ==\nShram Shakti Express runs with 1 AC 1 tier coach, 1 AC 2 tier coaches, 4 AC 3 tier coaches, 9 Sleeper coaches, 5 General coaches along with 2 EOG coaches. Thus, having a total of 22 LHB coaches. \n<br />\n\n== Traction ==\nThe normal locomotive of '''Shram Shakti''' is a [[Indian locomotive class WAP-7|WAP 4]] Locomotive of Kanpur shed. However due to non availability of WAP 4, it may sometimes get WAP 5 or WAP 7 of Kanpur locoshed.  \n\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Sleeper Class coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - Sleeper Class coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 1st class coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - AC 1st class coach\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General Deen Dayalu coach.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - General [[Deendayal Upadhyaya|Deen Dayalu coach]]\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board 2.jpg|12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board 2\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - General coach.jpg\nFile:12452 Shram Shakti Express - Train board.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express - AC 2 tier.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express - AC 3 tier.jpg\nFile:12451 Shram Shakti Express.jpg\nFile:Shram Shakti Express.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== Coaches ==\n[[Passenger car (rail)|Coach]] Composition are as follows-\n\n12451 CNB-NDLS\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"bac